<br>
 <br>
   Although bind sight is a minor item on the list of wizard issues Verant should be addressing<br>
the fact is that we already have an excessive number of spells which aren't worth the effort of casting, we can't afford to have any of our usefull spells reduced to that category.  Its also <br>
worth pointing out that identify and bind sight were the only spells we had which actually fit the 'masters of knowledge' description which Verant has given our class (its not an accident that I leave out eye of zomm and eye of tallon, their short durations and agro factor puts them on the list of spells not worth casting).<br>
<br>
  So yes, please fix bind sight and return it to its intended functionality.<br>
<br>
  Kulos<br>
